    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1966-12-24T01:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1966-12-24T01:15:00-05:00" n="199"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>199. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Kuwait</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d199fn1">Source: National Archives and Records
                        Administration, RG 59, Records of the Department of State, Central Files,
                        1964–66, PET 6 KUW. Confidential; Limdis. Repeated to London and
                        Tehran.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Kuwait City</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1966-12-24T06:15:00+00:00">December 24, 1966,
                        0615Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>662. Ref: Kuwait A–170, Dec 8, 1966; Tehran 2619, Dec 21.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d199fn2">Neither printed. (Ibid., PET 2 KUW and PET 6 IRAN,
                        respectively)</note> Protect source and limit use of substance:</p>
                <p>To assuage GOK fears that Iran’s publicized “victory” over the Consortium<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d199fn3">See <ref target="#d198fn2">footnote 2, Document
                            198</ref>.</note> would become hardship for Kuwait <gloss
                        target="#t_KOC1">KOC</gloss> Director permitted Oil-Finance Undersecretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_WA1">Abdul Wahab</persName> to read the agreement.
                    Undersecretary promised not to use info against companies or Iran and to deny
                    having had access through <gloss target="#t_KOC1">KOC</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_CHR1">Cottam</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
